# MCP TOOLS CONFIGURATION

<context>
**Purpose**: Configure Model Context Protocol (MCP) tools for file operations and terminal commands
**Target Audience**: Windsurf IDE users working with the OpenSCAD Tree-sitter project
**Integration**: These tools provide file system access and command execution capabilities
**Success Criteria**: Reliable file operations and command execution through MCP servers
</context>

## DESKTOP COMMANDER MCP - PRIMARY TOOL

<mcp_instructions>
**Use Desktop Commander MCP for all file operations and terminal commands:**

```bash
# IMPORTANT: Always prepend Set-Location to commands
execute_command({ "command": "Set-Location \"C:\\Users\\luciano\\git\\openscad-tree-sitter\"; nx run-many --target=build --all" })
execute_command({ "command": "Set-Location \"C:\\Users\\luciano\\git\\openscad-tree-sitter\"; nx run-many --target=test --all" })
execute_command({ "command": "Set-Location \"C:\\Users\\luciano\\git\\openscad-tree-sitter\"; nx test tree-sitter-openscad" })
execute_command({ "command": "Set-Location \"C:\\Users\\luciano\\git\\openscad-tree-sitter\"; nx test openscad-parser" })

# File operations (no Set-Location needed)
read_file({ "path": "src/file.ts" })
write_file({ "path": "src/file.ts", "content": "..." })
edit_block({ "edits": "file.ts\n<<<<<<< SEARCH\nold code\n=======\nnew code\n>>>>>>> REPLACE" })
search_files({ "pattern": "*.ts" })
search_code({ "pattern": "function name", "path": "src/" })
```

**CRITICAL: Desktop Commander Working Directory**
⚠️ **ALWAYS prepend** `Set-Location "C:\Users\luciano\git\openscad-tree-sitter";` to ANY command
⚠️ Desktop Commander does NOT start in the project directory
⚠️ **Example:** `Set-Location "C:\Users\luciano\git\openscad-tree-sitter"; nx test tree-sitter-openscad`

**Key tools:**
- `execute_command` - Run terminal commands
- `read_file` - Read file contents
- `write_file` - Write files
- `edit_block` - Make targeted edits
- `search_files` - Find files by name
- `search_code` - Search code patterns
- `list_directory` - List directory contents
- `create_directory` - Create directories
</mcp_instructions>

## FALLBACK: @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem

<filesystem_fallback>
**If Desktop Commander MCP fails, use the official filesystem server:**

```bash
# Install and use filesystem server
npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem /path/to/workspace
```

**Available tools:**
```bash
read_file({ "path": "src/file.ts" })
write_file({ "path": "src/file.ts", "content": "..." })
create_directory({ "path": "src/new-folder" })
list_directory({ "path": "src/" })
move_file({ "source": "old.ts", "destination": "new.ts" })
search_files({ "pattern": "*.ts", "path": "src/" })
get_file_info({ "path": "src/file.ts" })
```

**When to use:**
- Desktop Commander is unavailable or not working
- Need secure file operations with access controls
- Working in restricted environments
- Require standardized MCP filesystem operations
</filesystem_fallback>

## FINAL FALLBACK: When Both MCP Tools Fail

<final_fallback>
**If BOTH Desktop Commander MCP AND Filesystem Server fail:**

⚠️ **DO NOT RETRY** - Stop attempting to use MCP file tools
⚠️ **DO NOT REPEAT** - Avoid calling the same failed tools again

**Instead, inform the user:**
```
Both MCP file operation tools have failed:
1. Desktop Commander MCP - [error details]
2. @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem - [error details]

I cannot perform file operations directly. Please:
- Check your MCP server configuration
- Verify tool permissions and access
- Manually perform the required file operations
- Or provide file contents directly in the chat
```

**Alternative approaches:**
- Ask user to copy/paste file contents
- Request manual file operations
- Suggest using IDE or text editor directly
- Recommend checking MCP server setup
</final_fallback>

## MCP TROUBLESHOOTING

<troubleshooting>
**Common issues and solutions:**

**Desktop Commander not working:**
1. Check if Desktop Commander MCP server is running
2. Verify Windsurf MCP configuration
3. Ensure proper permissions for file system access
4. Try restarting Windsurf IDE

**Filesystem Server not working:**
1. Install the server: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem`
2. Check workspace path configuration
3. Verify Node.js and npm are properly installed
4. Check for permission issues

**Both tools failing:**
1. Check internet connection for npm packages
2. Verify system permissions
3. Try manual file operations
4. Contact support or check documentation
</troubleshooting>